snippet: The Iowa caucuses are a two-step process: first comes the voting, then comes the spinning.
abstract: The Iowa caucuses are a two-step process: first comes the voting, then comes the spinning.
lead_paragraph: Predicting the outcome of the Iowa caucuses is challenging enough. Six different Republican candidates -- Michele Bachmann, Herman Cain, Newt Gingrich, Ron Paul, Rick Perry and Mitt Romney -- have led at least one poll of the state at some point in this cycle. A seventh, Rick Santorum, is closing fast in the polls and has a realistic chance to win on Tuesday night.

headline.main: In Iowa, Six Candidates Compete to Beat Expectations
